
Yangtools WEB Site README
--------------------------

Version:  2008-07-18 (v0.9.3)

Pre-Build steps:

   - set netconf/src/platform/platform.profile details
      - CFLAGS has -ggdb3 for debug version (out for real)
      - CFLAGS has -DLINUX or -DMACOSX
      - CINC has /sw/include added for MACOSX

Build Variables:

  BLD: set to remove gdb synbols
  MAC: set to compile for MacOsX

  make BLD=BLD to make no-debug build on linux variants

  make BLD=BLD MAC=MAC to make no-debug on MacOsX

Current Build Sequence:

   - cd netconf/src
   - make *
   - su
   - make * install
   - cd ../modules
   - make all
   - cd ../../mysql
   - ./redo_mysql.sh
   - ./load_newmod.sh newmod.sql

 This will reset the entire WEBDOCS server
 TBD: incremental additions of modules

Run development WEB server
   - cd ../ncorg
   - ./start-ncorg.sh
     (runs WEBBrick on port 8080)

Run production WEB serverin background:
  Usually added to end of /etc/rc.local:
  (cd /path/to/trunk/ncorg; ./start-ncorg.sh prod.cfg&)

TBD: graceful CherryPy shutdown and restart via /etc/rc.d/init.d/

Run NETCONF Agent
  - TBD


External Installed Files:
   - /usr/bin/yangdump
   - /usr/local/bin/netconf-subsystem

External file dependencies:
   - /etc/services (for netconfd)
   - /etc/ssh/sshd_config
   - SELinux config to allow access to port 830
   - /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf (to proxy to WEBBrick as 'ncxserver')


